    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (76.67) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.91) serving as our undeniable anchors. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a high-upside environment against Rea, buoyed by positive wind conditions and an elite xwOBA profile that elevates his base projection significantly. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** thrives in his matchup against Gallen; the combination of a favorable park shift and a strong dynamic platoon advantage makes him a must-start core piece. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.40) rounds out our elite tier, utilizing a clean look at Cantillo to maximize his power potential, while **Miguel Vargas** (60.61) remains a high-floor play, capitalizing on a soft opposing arm in Irvin to solidify his spot at 1B.\n\nThe decision to bench **Coby Mayo** (46.33) was the tightest call on the board. While **Coby Mayo**\u2019s park-adjusted projection against Crochet held merit, the inherent risk of facing an elite arm suppressed his score just enough to keep him behind the more efficient profiles of **Josh Jung** and **Andy Pages**. We are closely monitoring the risks associated with **Gunnar Henderson** (52.11); despite his high offensive ceiling, the matchup against the sharp Crochet and a negative platoon split make him a volatile asset today. Furthermore, while we value the speed potential of **Heliot Ramos** (48.22), his limited offensive projection necessitates a cautious approach, and we have fully benched **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Brady House**, and **Nolan Schanuel** to protect our games-played caps as they failed to clear our 40.0 efficiency threshold against today\u2019s starting pitching.",
